l neighborhood.<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"block-link block-link--hotels \">\n                <div class=\"block-link__container\">\n\n                    <div class=\"salt-icon__container\">\n                        <span class=\"salt-icon salt-icon--hotels\"><\/span>\n                        <svg class=\"icon icon-round-shape\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-round-shape\"><\/use><\/svg>\n                    <\/div>\n\n                    <p><strong>Find all:<\/strong>&#xA0;<a href=\"https:\/\/saltinourhair.com\/go\/istanbul-all\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\">Hotels in Istanbul<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n                <\/div>\n            <\/div><\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<p>Are you planning to stay for longer than two days? Add Dolmabahce Palace, Ortak&#xF6;y Mosque, Beylerbeyi Palace and Prince Islands to your things to do in Istanbul. Unfortunately, due to bad weather, we did not have the option to visit these locations.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"648\" height=\"810\" src=\"https:\/\/saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/05\/istanbul-Karako&#x308;y-648x810.jpg\" alt=\"istanbul Karako&#x308;y\" class=\"wp-image-14413\"><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"648\" height=\"810\" src=\"https:\/\/saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/05\/istanbul-umbrella-street-Karako&#x308;y-648x810.jpg\" alt=\"istanbul umbrella street Karako&#x308;y\" class=\"wp-image-14414\"><\/figure>\n<\/figure>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h2 id=\"transport\">How to get around Istanbul<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Istanbul offers many ways of getting around by public transport. The metro, bus, and tram run throughout the entire city. Ferries are also a 